{
  "texts": [
    "The full text of each study is assessed for eligibility (15 excluded) and each study is validated based on whether it performs research on unit test generation using large language models (2 excluded).",
    "Results of systematic literature reviewIn the emerging application of using Large Language Models for generating unit tests and the limited research in this domain, this study instead aims to examine the increasing adoption of LLMs in code generation tasks.",
    "By performing a literature review in Section 2 it was observed, that only 9 studies were retrieved.",
    "This result wouldn't yield sufficient data to analyze the popularity of LLM's.",
    "A more abstract term \"code generation\" was selected to retrieve a larger number of studies (SQ1), improving the overall accuracy of the chronological distribution of the papers diagram in Figure 2."
  ]
}